    "title": "Impairments push Lafarge Africa to 2017 loss, shares fall",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "LAGOS, April 9 (Reuters) - Lafarge Africa has taken a one-off impairment in Nigeria and South Africa totalling around 33 billion naira ($105 million), widening its loss before tax for 2017 from a year earlier and sending its shares tumbling.\nBruno Bayet, chief financial officer, told Reuters the impairments accounted for bulk of the loss, without which the cement maker would have turned a profit.\nLafarge Africa shares listed on the Lagos bourse fell to a one-year low on the news.\n$1 = 314.50 naira Reporting by Chijioke Ohuocha; Editing by Alexis Akwagyiram and Mark Potter\n ",
